Ok I found a workaround adding `$this->primaryModel->__unset($relationName);` to reset the $relationName property if there is a $callable.

db/ActiveRelationTrait.php:105 From:
```
    public function via($relationName, callable $callable = null)
    {
        $relation = $this->primaryModel->getRelation($relationName);
        $this->via = [$relationName, $relation];
        if ($callable !== null) {
            call_user_func($callable, $relation);
        }

        return $this;
    }
```

To:

```
    public function via($relationName, callable $callable = null)
    {
        $relation = $this->primaryModel->getRelation($relationName);
        $this->via = [$relationName, $relation];
        if ($callable !== null) {
            $this->primaryModel->__unset($relationName);
            call_user_func($callable, $relation);
        }

        return $this;
    }
```

Seems to work in my test env.

